'''Boss kill count''', '''boss killcount''' or '''boss kc''' (listed on the [[HiScores]] as '''Score''') refers to the total amount of times a [[boss]] has been slain by the player. [[Raids]] and [[skilling bosses]] are also commonly referred to as boss kc, despite not always following the same structure as traditional bosses.

Almost all bosses have dedicated in-game [[Combat achievements|combat achievement]] pages as well as a [[collection log]], both of which display the [[Player character|player]]’s kill count alongside other useful information, such as obtained drops.

== Ranking ==
A player’s '''score''' does not necessarily mean they have a '''rank'''. While both are recorded in the [[HiScores]], a score only indicates that the player has recorded kills or completions for that boss, whereas a rank is only assigned once that kill count is high enough relative to other players to place in the rankings. Obtaining a rank typically requires 5 kills, although this is only 1 kill for [[Tz-Kal Zuk]].

== History ==
The boss kill count feature was added to the [[HiScores]] on [[5 December]] [[2019]]. The release of the Boss HiScores caused the HiScore pages to become under heavy load, making them load and update slowly. To mitigate this, [[Jagex]] initially raised the minimum kill count required for bosses to appear on the HiScores to 50. Following subsequent behind-the-scenes improvements, this requirement was gradually lowered. All bosses and activities now require only 1 kill count to appear.

